 Al-Hikmah University, Ilorin has unveiled an  online radio station to be managed by Department of Mass Communication. The radio station, however,  began services last Wednesday. This was made known on the institution’s Twitter handle. The Vice-chancellor, Prof. Noah Yusuf launched the online radio which can be downloaded on Google Playstore. The application is data-free on Google Play Store for MTN users in the country. The application can be downloaded by searching Al-Hikmah Radio.